# flutter core

- Keep widgets small, focused, and easy to reason about. Break oversized screens into reusable UI pieces and clear state boundaries.
- Prefer explicit state-management boundaries and dependency wiring over implicit cross-feature coupling.
- Respect Material 3 and platform idioms together, following the existing app design language.
- Keep navigation, validation, loading, error, and empty states explicit in the UI flow.
- Design for localization, accessibility, testing, and performance from the start rather than treating them as follow-up work.
- Use null safety deliberately and keep asynchronous flows, side effects, and state updates easy to trace.
- Make business logic testable outside the widget tree and use widget or integration tests on critical flows where practical.
